{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nKeep the single-instance bot alive under hangs, controllable in an incident, and ‚Äî critically ‚Äî **crash-safe**: a restart must never double-submit or strand a stack. This is the reliability-fallback backbone. Split out of S5 (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/autolander/loop.py` ‚Äî EDIT: heartbeat write, emergency-stop sentinel check, SIGTERM drain + recovery-record write, restart-recovery reconciliation.\n- `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` ‚Äî EDIT: add the `HEALTHCHECK` line (the file itself is created NEW by sibling **S5a**; this task `depends_on` S5a so the create precedes this edit).\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml` ‚Äî EDIT: set `stop_grace_period: 120s` on the autolander service (so the SIGTERM drain can write `recovery.json`).\n- `infra/autolander/tests/test_crash_recovery.py` ‚Äî NEW: the crash-recovery/idempotency test suite (kill-at-each-phase + the drain‚áÑautoheal-race case).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] **Heartbeat (AC5):** the bot writes a timestamp file in the state volume once per its 15 s poll (S2 cadence); its age is served as `heartbeat_age_s` by S5c's status endpoint. Contract: freshness ‚â§ 15 s; `land`'s `lander_down` treats age **> 90 s** (6√ó poll) as down.\n- [ ] **Liveness/restart (AC4):** a `HEALTHCHECK` marks the container `unhealthy` on a **hang** by stat-ing the **local heartbeat file** (unhealthy if older than the staleness threshold) ‚Äî it MUST NOT probe Gerrit (a Gerrit outage would flap restarts). The `willfarrell/autoheal` sidecar (S5a) restarts the `autoheal=true`-labeled container on `unhealthy`.\n- [ ] **Emergency-stop (prior art: Zuul `pause`):** an emergency-stop **sentinel file** in the state volume (presence = stop; operator creates to pause, removes to resume) transitions the bot to `paused` (the S2 `phase` value) ‚Äî STOPS consuming new `Autosubmit` changes. Lives on the state volume so a redeploy does not silently un-pause.\n- [ ] **Drain-on-shutdown + crash-safe recovery (RELIABILITY FALLBACK):** on SIGTERM the bot's **FIRST action is to write the recovery record** `recovery.json` to the state volume (the `wipChain` snapshot ‚Äî `change_id`, `chain_member_ids`, `tested_shas`, `phase`, `re_drive_count`, and the S3 handback `acknowledged` flag) ‚Äî written up-front so recovery is guaranteed no matter what interrupts the drain. It then attempts a graceful finish of an already-near-complete submit + S3 outcome write (prior art: Zuul `graceful`), time-bounded to **120 s**, with the compose service set to **`stop_grace_period: 120s`** so `docker compose stop/down` does not SIGKILL early.\n- [ ] **Drain ‚áÑ autoheal race (must not fight each other):** during the drain the bot **keeps writing its heartbeat each tick** so the HEALTHCHECK stays healthy and autoheal is not provoked into a mid-drain `docker restart` (autoheal's `docker restart` does NOT honour `stop_grace_period`). And because `recovery.json` is written FIRST, even if autoheal *does* restart the bot mid-drain, recovery is still safe (the restart path below reconciles it). Belt-and-suspenders: no interruption can strand a stack.\n- [ ] **Restart reconciliation** ‚Äî on restart the bot reads `recovery.json` + reconciles against LIVE Gerrit and S3's markers BEFORE selecting new work, with a rule for every interruption point:\n  - `phase=rebasing` ‚Äî discard the in-memory `wipChain` and **re-select from scratch** (`Autosubmit` still set, Gerrit holds the current patchset). No submit happened; nothing to undo.\n  - `phase=awaiting_verified` ‚Äî discard in-memory state and **re-select**; the change is still `Autosubmit`+needs-fresh-`Verified`, so the loop re-enters `awaiting_verified` for the same patchset. Idempotent; no submit happened.\n  - `phase=submitting` ‚Äî check LIVE Gerrit: all members `MERGED` ‚Üí write the `merged` outcome/ack; not merged ‚Üí **re-drive**. Never blindly re-issue submit.\n  - **an incomplete hand-back** (detected by an S3 marker with `acknowledged=false` ‚Äî NOT a `wipChain` phase value) ‚Äî complete the idempotent `Autosubmit`-removal across the stack, then set `acknowledged=true`.\n  No double-submit; no stranded stack.\n- [ ] **Crash-recovery/idempotency test (the reliability guarantee):** an automated test kills the bot at each `wipChain` phase (`rebasing`, `awaiting_verified`, `submitting`) **and during an in-flight hand-back** (S3 marker `acknowledged=false`), and asserts the restarted instance neither double-submits nor strands a stack, and converges the S3 marker to `acknowledged=true`. A dedicated case asserts the **drain‚áÑautoheal race is benign**: a SIGTERM followed by an autoheal `docker restart` mid-drain still recovers cleanly (because `recovery.json` is written first)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783844318431879001,"uuid":"233206b7-8220-45da-b39f-8609eb62c7e8"}